 Four balaclava-clad men overpowered two female guards around 01:00 last Sunday morning. The men demanded weapons but the two officers denied carrying weapons.
They then proceeded to frisk the officers and found both their service pistols hidden under their clothes. Also read: Armed robbery at Auctioneers The department has denied that the depot itself had been breached by the robbers.
The men made off without hurting either of the women on duty. Also read: Father kills two robbers after being stabbed in his Aerorand home The two female security officers work for Mafoko Security Patrols who have been contracted by the department to secure the depot.
Depot employees said that they received a circular from the department last Monday alerting them of the robbery. Police say that one of the robbers may have worked for the depot, but the investigation has not rendered any positive results yet. •No arrests have been made.  Armed robbery at Auctioneers Pastor gunned down during church service Three killed in shootout with Police Suspects might be linked to seven other robberies • Save our standby number (072 248 3855) and send us a WhatsApp message with the words “Add me” to be added to our broadcast list. • Like us on Facebook, follow us on Twitter and Instagram. • Subscribe to our YouTube channel. • Click on the link to subscribe to our bi-weekly newsletter via email. Contact our news room on our 24 hr standby number 072 248 3855, or send a mail to our editor tobie@mobserver.co.za